State Bank of Mauritius Ltd. (SBM) , the
countryâ€™s second-largest lender by market value, said it
received a 30 million-euro credit facility from the European
Investment Bank.  The money will help finance long-term, export-oriented
projects in the Indian Ocean island nation, the Port Louis-based
bank said in an e-mailed statement today. The company obtained a
20 million-euro loan from the EIB in 2005, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
